## M20a negative: consuming receiver without explicit `<`.
##
## Calling a method declared `sub consume(self: User)` from a
## bare lvalue requires the call site to write `(<u).consume()`.
## Bare `u.consume()` must error — consumption (move) is dramatic
## enough to deserve a visible marker.
##
## EXPECTED: sema error pointing at the method name in the call.

struct User
  name: String

  sub consume(self: User)
    print(self.name)

sub main()
  u = User(name: "Steve")
  u.consume()
